Grated apple provides an easy way to add taste and texture to a burger. Perfectly crispy
chips and a fresh cucumber side salad are also welcome additions to this dish.

== Chips ==

Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{400%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips
(no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season
with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in one layer.

Cook on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Salad ==

Meanwhile, cut the @apple{1}(quartered and cored) into quarters and remove the core.

Coarsely grate one-quarter of the apple and set aside. Cut the remaining apple
lengthways into thin slices.

Cut the @cucumber{1}(halved lengthways, seeded and thinly sliced) in half lengthways
and remove the seeds with a spoon. Cut into thin slices.

Peel then slice the @onion{1}(peeled and sliced into thin rings) into thin rings.

In a large #bowl{} for the salad, mix together the @balsamic vinegar{1%sachet},
a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Just before serving toss the cucumber, half the @salad leaves{20%grams} and half
the apple slices through the dressing.

== Burgers ==

In a large bowl, combine the @Irish beef mince{250%grams} with the grated apple
and the @breadcrumbs{1%pack}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after
handling raw mince.

Season with salt and pepper and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

== Cooking ==

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once the oil is hot, add the burgers and fry until browned on the outside and
cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes} in total.

Carefully turn them every ~{3-4%minutes} and lower the heat if needed. IMPORTANT:
The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm for ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

To assemble the burgers, spread a spoonful of @mayo{2%sachets} over each base
bun.

Top with beef patty, remaining salad leaves, apple slices and onion. Close with
the top bun.

Serve with chips and salad alongside.